8px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p><br></p><p>Korean skin care routines are known for being rigorous and involving multiple steps. I know it might seem overwhelming at first, but trust me, it's worth it. <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 241, 229);">Korean skin care routines are designed to be customized to your specific skin concerns and needs</span>.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Routines commonly range from <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold;">3 to 10 steps</span>.&nbsp;<span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Each step is carefully chosen to address a specific aspect of your skin, like removing makeup and impurities, providing hydration and nourishment to the skin, and protecting the skin from UV damage. &nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><span style="color: inherit;">Read more about the full </span><a href="https://koreanskincare.nl/blogs/skintalks/full-10-step-routine" class=""><u style="color: rgb(255, 138, 5);">Korean skin care 10-step routine</u></a><span style="color: inherit;">!</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><span style="color: inherit;"><br></span></span></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679404125871" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679404125871" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1653642484175" data-id="1653642484175"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679404125838" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1679404125838"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 25px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 12.5px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 26px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-5051" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Less fragrance, more minimalistic ingredients</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679404125914" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679404125914"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p><font face="Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></p><p><span style="font-family: Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif;">One of the things that sets Korean skin care apart from Western skin care products is its <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 241, 229);">minimalistic approach to ingredients</span>. Korean skin care brands believe that <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 241, 229);">less is more</span> when it comes to the ingredients used in skin care products. This means that you'll often find products with a shorter ingredient list, containing only the essentials for your skin's needs.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family: Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-family: Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif;">Additionally, many&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif; color: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">brands are also moving away from using heavy fragrances in their products, recognizing that they can be a potential irritant for some people's skin. By focusing on simple, minimalistic ingredients, Korean skin care brands can provide 